{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775906924140,"sessionID":"ses_283b3175effeZmoEnkR6wnhZW5","part":{"id":"prt_d7c4d1d2f001SQkKsrIh953BI4","messageID":"msg_d7c4cffbb001L9YeTC8BouWL7J","sessionID":"ses_283b3175effeZmoEnkR6wnhZW5","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/spec.yaml"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/spec.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: AR-028\n2: title: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n3: module: sdk-python\n4: language: Python\n5: size: M\n6: status: open\n7: \n8: # AR-028: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n9: # Module: sdk-python\n10: # Language: Python\n11: # Size: M\n12: \n13: # OpenSpec Metadata\n14: openspec:\n15:   version: \"1.0\"\n16:   project: agentcube\n17: \n18: # Architecture Requirement\n19: requirement:\n20:   type: client-sdk\n21:   description: |\n22:     Implement an AgentRuntimeClient class within the sdk-python module to provide\n23:     a Python SDK for interacting with the AgentRuntime service. This client will\n24:     enable developers to programmatically create, manage, and monitor agents\n25:     through a clean, Pythonic API that abstracts the underlying gRPC/HTTP\n26:     communication with the AgentRuntime.\n27: \n28: # Scope\n29: scope:\n30:   in:\n31:     - AgentRuntimeClient class implementation\n32:     - Agent lifecycle management (create, start, stop, delete)\n33:     - Agent configuration and deployment APIs\n34:     - Event streaming and monitoring capabilities\n35:     - Error handling and retry logic\n36:     - Async/sync API support\n37:     - Type hints and pydantic models for all API objects\n38:   out:\n39:     - CLI tool for agent management (separate AR)\n40:     - Authentication/authorization implementation (assumes existing)\n41:     - WebSocket-based real-time updates (separate AR)\n42:     - Multi-region failover handling (separate AR)\n43: \n44: # Acceptance Criteria\n45: acceptance:\n46:   - AgentRuntimeClient provides clean, Pythonic API for all runtime operations\n47:   - Both synchronous and asynchronous APIs are supported\n48:   - Comprehensive type hints for IDE support and type checking\n49:   - Proper error handling with custom exception hierarchy\n50:   - Retry logic with exponential backoff for transient failures\n51:   - Event streaming supports real-time agent status updates\n52:   - Unit and integration test coverage >= 80%\n53:   - Documentation with usage examples\n54: \n55: # References\n56: references:\n57:   - https://docs.pydantic.dev/\n58:   - https://grpc.io/docs/languages/python/\n59:   - https://www.python-httpx.org/\n60: \n61: # Estimation\n62: estimation:\n63:   size: M\n64:   story_points: 5\n65:   days: 3\n\n(End of file - total 65 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: AR-028\ntitle: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\nmodule: sdk-python\nlanguage: Python\nsize: M\nstatus: open\n\n# AR-028: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n# Module: sdk-python\n# Language: Python\n# Size: M\n\n# OpenSpec Metadata\nopenspec:\n  version: \"1.0\"\n  project: agentcube\n\n# Architecture Requirement\nrequirement:\n  type: client-sdk","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/spec.yaml","time":{"start":1775906924118,"end":1775906924139}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775906924143,"sessionID":"ses_283b3175effeZmoEnkR6wnhZW5","part":{"id":"prt_d7c4d21be001lRAndV4gzfl0q4","messageID":"msg_d7c4cffbb001L9YeTC8BouWL7J","sessionID":"ses_283b3175effeZmoEnkR6wnhZW5","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-028 Delta Specification: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This document specifies the delta changes required to implement the AgentRuntimeClient SDK for Python.\n6: \n7: ## New Components\n8: \n9: ### 1. AgentRuntimeClient Class\n10: \n11: **Location:** `sdk-python/src/agentcube/client/runtime_client.py`\n12: \n13: **Description:** Main client class for interacting with the AgentRuntime service.\n14: \n15: **Key Methods:**\n16: - `create_agent(config: AgentConfig) -> Agent`\n17: - `start_agent(agent_id: str) -> AgentStatus`\n18: - `stop_agent(agent_id: str) -> AgentStatus`\n19: - `delete_agent(agent_id: str) -> None`\n20: - `get_agent(agent_id: str) -> Agent`\n21: - `list_agents(filters: AgentFilter) -> List[Agent]`\n22: - `stream_events(agent_id: str) -> Iterator[AgentEvent]`\n23: \n24: ### 2. Configuration Models\n25: \n26: **Location:** `sdk-python/src/agentcube/models/config.py`\n27: \n28: **Description:** Pydantic models for agent configuration.\n29: \n30: **Classes:**\n31: - `AgentConfig`\n32: - `AgentResources`\n33: - `AgentEnvironment`\n34: \n35: ### 3. Response Models\n36: \n37: **Location:** `sdk-python/src/agentcube/models/responses.py`\n38: \n39: **Description:** Pydantic models for API responses.\n40: \n41: **Classes:**\n42: - `Agent`\n43: - `AgentStatus`\n44: - `AgentEvent`\n45: - `AgentFilter`\n46: \n47: ### 4. Exception Hierarchy\n48: \n49: **Location:** `sdk-python/src/agentcube/exceptions.py`\n50: \n51: **Description:** Custom exceptions for error handling.\n52: \n53: **Classes:**\n54: - `AgentRuntimeError` (base)\n55: - `AgentNotFoundError`\n56: - `AgentCreationError`\n57: - `ConnectionError`\n58: - `AuthenticationError`\n59: \n60: ### 5. Retry Logic\n61: \n62: **Location:** `sdk-python/src/agentcube/client/retry.py`\n63: \n64: **Description:** Retry decorator and utilities.\n65: \n66: ## Modified Components\n67: \n68: None - this is a new feature implementation.\n69: \n70: ## Interface Contracts\n71: \n72: ### gRPC/HTTP Endpoints\n73: \n74: The client will communicate with the following endpoints:\n75: \n76: - `POST /v1/agents` - Create agent\n77: - `GET /v1/agents/{id}` - Get agent\n78: - `DELETE /v1/agents/{id}` - Delete agent\n79: - `POST /v1/agents/{id}/start` - Start agent\n80: - `POST /v1/agents/{id}/stop` - Stop agent\n81: - `GET /v1/agents` - List agents\n82: - `GET /v1/agents/{id}/events` - Stream events\n83: \n84: ## Dependencies\n85: \n86: - `httpx` or `aiohttp` for HTTP client\n87: - `pydantic` for data validation\n88: - `tenacity` for retry logic\n\n(End of file - total 88 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-028 Delta Specification: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document specifies the delta changes required to implement the AgentRuntimeClient SDK for Python.\n\n## New Components\n\n### 1. AgentRuntimeClient Class\n\n**Location:** `sdk-python/src/agentcube/client/runtime_client.py`\n\n**Description:** Main client class for interacting with the AgentRuntime service.\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- `create_agent(config: AgentConfig) -> Agent`\n- `start_agent(agent_id: str) -> AgentStatus`\n- `stop_agent(agent_id: str) -> AgentStatus`\n- `delete_agent(agent_id: str) -> None`\n- `get_agent(agent_id: str) -> Agent`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775906924122,"end":1775906924141}}}}
