ication | Est. |\n34: |---|------|--------------|------|\n35: | 3.2.1 | Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/models/config.py` | File exists | 0.1h |\n36: | 3.2.2 | Implement `AgentConfig` Pydantic model | Model with name, image, env vars fields | 0.5h |\n37: | 3.2.3 | Implement `AgentResources` Pydantic model | CPU, memory, GPU fields with validators | 0.5h |\n38: | 3.2.4 | Implement `AgentEnvironment` Pydantic model | Environment variables dict with validation | 0.5h |\n39: | 3.2.5 | Add `AgentConfig` validators (required fields, format) | Invalid configs raise ValidationError | 0.5h |\n40: | 3.2.6 | Add JSON schema export for `AgentConfig` | `.model_json_schema()` works | 0.25h |\n41: \n42: **Deliverable:** Config models defined with validation.\n43: \n44: ---\n45: \n46: ## ST-3.3 — Data Model Definitions (Responses)\n47: \n48: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n49: |---|------|--------------|------|\n50: | 3.3.1 | Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/models/responses.py` | File exists | 0.1h |\n51: | 3.3.2 | Implement `AgentStatus` Enum | PENDING, RUNNING, STOPPED, ERROR states | 0.25h |\n52: | 3.3.3 | Implement `Agent` Pydantic model | id, name, status, config, created_at fields | 0.5h |\n53: | 3.3.4 | Implement `AgentEvent` Pydantic model | timestamp, type, payload fields | 0.5h |\n54: | 3.3.5 | Implement `AgentFilter` Pydantic model | status, name_pattern, tags fields | 0.5h |\n55: | 3.3.6 | Add response model validators | Datetime parsing, enum validation | 0.25h |\n56: | 3.3.7 | Export all models from `models/__init__.py` | `from agentcube.models import AgentConfig, Agent` works | 0.1h |\n57: \n58: **Deliverable:** Response models defined with validation.\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ## ST-3.4 — Exception Hierarchy\n63: \n64: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n65: |---|------|--------------|------|\n66: | 3.4.1 | Implement `AgentRuntimeError` base exception | Base class with message, code attrs | 0.25h |\n67: | 3.4.2 | Implement `AgentNotFoundError` (404) | Raised when agent ID not found | 0.25h |\n68: | 3.4.3 | Implement `AgentCreationError` (400/422) | Raised when creation fails | 0.25h |\n69: | 3.4.4 | Implement `ConnectionError` (network) | Raised on transport failures | 0.25h |\n70: | 3.4.5 | Implement `AuthenticationError` (401/403) | Raised on auth failures | 0.25h |\n71: | 3.4.6 | Implement `ValidationError` (400) | Raised on request validation failures | 0.25h |\n72: | 3.4.7 | Export all exceptions from `exceptions.py` | `from agentcube.exceptions import AgentRuntimeError` works | 0.1h |\n73: | 3.4.8 | Add HTTP status code mapping | Each exception has `.status_code` property | 0.25h |\n74: \n75: **Deliverable:** Exception hierarchy defined and exportable.\n76: \n77: ---\n78: \n79: ## ST-3.5 — Base Client Foundation\n80: \n81: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n82: |---|------|--------------|------|\n83: | 3.5.1 | Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/client/base.py` | File exists | 0.1h |\n84: | 3.5.2 | Implement `BaseClient.__init__()` with base_url, api_key, timeout | Attributes stored correctly | 0.5h |\n85: | 3.5.3 | Implement `_build_url()` method | URL construction works for endpoints | 0.25h |\n86: | 3.5.4 | Implement `_build_headers()` method | Auth header included when api_key set | 0.25h |\n87: | 3.5.5 | Add logging infrastructure | Logger created with module name | 0.25h |\n88: | 3.5.6 | Implement `_handle_response_error()` method | Maps HTTP errors to exceptions | 0.5h |\n89: | 3.5.7 | Add request/response serialization helpers | JSON encoding/decoding works | 0.25h |\n90: \n91: **Deliverable:** Base client with common functionality.\n92: \n93: ---\n94: \n95: ## ST-3.6 — Sync Client Implementation\n96: \n97: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n98: |---|------|--------------|------|\n99: | 3.6.1 | Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/client/runtime_client.py` | File exists | 0.1h |\n100: | 3.6.2 | Implement `AgentRuntimeClient` class extending BaseClient | Class defined with proper inheritance | 0.25h |\n101: | 3.6