\n377: - [ ] Package installs successfully (`pip install -e sdk-python/`)\n378: - [ ] AgentRuntimeClient importable from `agentcube.client`\n379: - [ ] AsyncAgentRuntimeClient importable from `agentcube.client`\n380: - [ ] All unit tests pass (>80% coverage)\n381: - [ ] All integration tests pass\n382: - [ ] Type checking passes (`mypy`)\n383: - [ ] Linting passes (`ruff`)\n384: - [ ] Documentation complete with docstrings\n385: - [ ] Usage examples in README\n386: \n387: ---\n388: \n389: ## Dependencies\n390: \n391: - `httpx>=0.25.0` — HTTP client (sync + async)\n392: - `pydantic>=2.0.0` — Data validation (already in pyproject.toml)\n393: - `tenacity>=8.2.0` — Retry logic\n394: - `pytest>=7.4.0` — Testing framework (already present)\n395: - `pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0` — Async test support\n396: - `pytest-httpx>=0.22.0` — HTTP mocking for tests\n397: - `respx>=0.20.0` — HTTPX mocking (optional alternative)\n398: \n399: ---\n400: \n401: ## Notes\n402: \n403: - Follow existing code style in sdk-python\n404: - Ensure type hints on all public methods\n405: - Use `httpx` for both sync and async HTTP (unified API)\n406: - Keep models immutable where possible (frozen=True)\n407: - Document all raised exceptions in docstrings\n408: \n409: ---\n410: \n411: *AR-028 — Module: sdk-python — Language: Python — Size: M*\n\n(End of file - total 411 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n> **AR ID:** AR-028\n> **Module:** `sdk-python`\n> **Language:** Python\n> **Size:** M\n> **Stage:** ST-3 (Design Completed)\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nImplement an `AgentRuntimeClient` class within the `sdk-python` module to provide a Python SDK for interacting with the AgentRuntime service. This client enables developers to programmatically create, manage, and monitor agents through a clean, Pythonic API with both synchronous and asynchronous support.\n\n---\n\n## ST-3.1 — Project Structure Setup\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775906932695,"end":1775906932718}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775906932722,"sessionID":"ses_283b3175effeZmoEnkR6wnhZW5","part":{"id":"prt_d7c4d39f0001FH4aGvgKBzmiEJ","messageID":"msg_d7c4d26ad001FWFbBmYxJ0qU4Z","sessionID":"ses_283b3175effeZmoEnkR6wnhZW5","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/tests.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/tests.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-028 Test Specification: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n2: \n3: ## Test Strategy\n4: \n5: ### Unit Tests\n6: \n7: #### 1. Model Validation Tests\n8: - Test `AgentConfig` validation\n9:   - Valid configurations pass\n10:   - Invalid configurations raise ValidationError\n11:   - Default values applied correctly\n12: \n13: - Test response model parsing\n14:   - Parse valid JSON responses\n15:   - Handle missing optional fields\n16:   - Handle malformed responses\n17: \n18: #### 2. Client Method Tests\n19: - Test `create_agent()`\n20:   - Success case returns Agent\n21:   - Server error raises appropriate exception\n22:   - Network error triggers retry\n23:   - Invalid config raises ValidationError\n24: \n25: - Test `get_agent()`\n26:   - Success case returns Agent\n27:   - Not found raises AgentNotFoundError\n28:   - Parse error raises ResponseError\n29: \n30: - Test `list_agents()`\n31:   - Success case returns List[Agent]\n32:   - Filters applied correctly\n33:   - Pagination handled properly\n34: \n35: - Test `start_agent()` / `stop_agent()`\n36:   - Success updates status\n37:   - Invalid state transitions handled\n38:   - Errors propagated correctly\n39: \n40: - Test `delete_agent()`\n41:   - Success returns None\n42:   - Not found handled appropriately\n43: \n44: #### 3. Retry Logic Tests\n45: - Test exponential backoff\n46: - Test max retry limit\n47: - Test non-retryable errors\n48: - Test circuit breaker\n49: \n50: #### 4. Async Client Tests\n51: - Test all sync methods have async equivalents\n52: - Test concurrent requests\n53: - Test async context manager\n54: \n55: #### 5. Event Streaming Tests\n56: - Test event parsing\n57: - Test connection errors\n58: - Test reconnection logic\n59: - Test proper cleanup\n60: \n61: ### Integration Tests\n62: \n63: #### 1. Mock Server Tests\n64: - Start mock server\n65: - Test full CRUD flow\n66: - Test error scenarios\n67: \n68: #### 2. End-to-End Tests\n69: - Test against real (staging) API if available\n70: - Verify authentication flow\n71: - Test rate limiting behavior\n72: \n73: ## Test Coverage Goals\n74: \n75: - Overall coverage: >= 80%\n76: - Client methods: 100%\n77: - Model validation: 100%\n78: - Error handling: 100%\n79: \n80: ## Test Files Structure\n81: \n82: ```\n83: sdk-python/tests/\n84: ├── unit/\n85: │   ├── test_models.py\n86: │   ├── test_client.py\n87: │   ├── test_async_client.py\n88: │   ├── test_retry.py\n89: │   └── test_exceptions.py\n90: ├── integration/\n91: │   ├── test_client_integration.py\n92: │   └── conftest.py\n93: └── fixtures/\n94:     ├── agent_config.json\n95:     └── agent_response.json\n96: ```\n97: \n98: ## Key Test Cases\n99: \n100: ### TC001: Create Agent Success\n101: ```python\n102: client = AgentRuntimeClient(base_url=\"http://localhost:8080\")\n103: config = AgentConfig(name=\"test-agent\", image=\"python:3.9\")\n104: agent = client.create_agent(config)\n105: assert agent.id is not None\n106: assert agent.name == \"test-agent\"\n107: assert agent.status == AgentStatus.CREATED\n108: ```\n109: \n110: ### TC002: Create Agent Validation Error\n111: ```python\n112: client = AgentRuntimeClient(base_url=\"http://localhost:8080\")\n113: config = AgentConfig(name=\"\", image=\"python:3.9\")  # Invalid: empty name\n114: with pytest.raises(ValidationError):\n115:     client.create_agent(config)\n116: ```\n117: \n118: ### TC003: Get Agent Not Found\n119: ```python\n120: client = AgentRuntimeClient(base_url=\"http://localhost:8080\")\n121: with pytest.raises(AgentNotFoundError):\n122:     client.get_agent(\"non-existent-id\")\n123: ```\n124: \n125: ### TC004: Retry on Network Error\n126: ```python\n127: # Mock transport to fail twice then succeed\n128: client = AgentRuntimeClient(base_url=\"http://localhost:8080\", max_retries=3)\n129: agent = client.get_agent(\"test-id\")  # Should retry and succeed\n130: ```\n131: \n132: ### TC005: Async Client Flow\n133: ```python\n134: async def test_async_create():\n135:     client = AsyncAgentRuntimeClient(base_url=\"http://localhost:8080\")\n136:     config = AgentConfig(name=\"test-agent\", image=\"python:3.9\")\n137:     agent = await client.create_agent(config)\n138:     assert agent.id is not None\n139: ```\n\n(End of file - total 139 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-028 Test Specification: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n## Test Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n#### 1. Model Validation Tests\n- Test `AgentConfig` validation\n  - Valid configurations pass\n  - Invalid configurations raise ValidationError\n  - Default values applied correctly\n\n- Test response model parsing\n  - Parse valid JSON responses\n  - Handle missing optional fields\n  - Handle malformed responses\n\n#### 2. Client Method Tests\n- Test `create_agent()`\n  - Success case returns Agent","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/tests.md","time":{"start":1775906932697,"end":1775906932720}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775906932723,"sessionID":"ses_283b3175effeZmoEnkR6wnhZW5","part":{"id":"prt_d7c4d3e88001uZOvCHabkklmOM","messageID":"msg_d7c4d26ad001FWFbBmYxJ0qU4Z","sessionID":"ses_283b3175effeZmoEnkR6wnhZW5","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/notes.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/notes.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-028 Notes: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n2: \n3: ## Created\n4: Date: 2026-04-11\n5: \n6: ## Context\n7: \n8: This change implements the Python SDK client for the AgentRuntime service. The client will provide both synchronous and asynchronous APIs for managing agent lifecycle, configuration, and monitoring.\n9: \n10: ## Design Decisions\n11: \n12: ### HTTP vs gRPC\n13: Initially considering HTTP/REST for broader compatibility, but gRPC may be evaluated if performance becomes critical.\n14: \n15: ### Library Choices\n16: - **HTTP Client**: `httpx` - supports both sync and async, modern API\n17: - **Validation**: `pydantic` - already used in project, excellent type support\n18: - **Retry**: `tenacity` - battle-tested, flexible retry strategies\n19: \n20: ## Open Questions\n21: \n22: 1. What is the exact API endpoint structure for the AgentRuntime service?\n23: 2. Are there existing API specifications (OpenAPI/Swagger) to reference?\n24: 3. What authentication mechanism should the client support?\n25: 4. Should we support connection pooling for high-throughput scenarios?\n26: \n27: ## References\n28: \n29: - Project: agentcube\n30: - Module: sdk-python\n31: - Language: Python 3.9+\n\n(End of file - total 31 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-028 Notes: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n## Created\nDate: 2026-04-11\n\n## Context\n\nThis change implements the Python SDK client for the AgentRuntime service. The client will provide both synchronous and asynchronous APIs for managing agent lifecycle, configuration, and monitoring.\n\n## Design Decisions\n\n### HTTP vs gRPC\nInitially considering HTTP/REST for broader compatibility, but gRPC may be evaluated if performance becomes critical.\n\n### Library Choices\n- **HTTP Client**: `httpx` - supports both sync and async, modern API\n- **Validation**: `pydantic` - already used in project, excellent type support\n- **Retry**: `tenacity` - battle-tested, flexible retry strategies\n\n## Open Questions","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/notes.md","time":{"start":1775906932699,"end":1775906932722}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775906932726,"sessionID":"ses_283b3175effeZmoEnkR6wnhZW5","part":{"id":"prt_d7c4d43490017AQTmgcxjRDnOK","messageID":"msg_d7c4d26ad001FWFbBmYxJ0qU4Z","sessionID":"ses_283b3175effeZmoEnkR6wnhZW5","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-028 Design: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n2: \n3: ## Architecture\n4: \n5: ```\n6: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n7: │                    AgentRuntimeClient                        │\n8: │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐       │\n9: │  │ Sync Client  │  │ Async Client │  │  Streaming   │       │\n10: │  └──────┬───────┘  └──────┬───────┘  └──────┬───────┘       │\n11: │         └──────────────────┴──────────────────┘              │\n12: │                            │                                 │\n13: │  ┌─────────────────────────┴─────────────────────────┐       │\n14: │  │              Transport Layer (HTTP/gRPC)           │       │\n15: │  │  ┌────────────┐  ┌────────────┐  ┌────────────┐   │       │\n16: │  │  │  Request   │  │   Retry    │  │  Circuit   │   │       │\n17: │  │  │  Builder   │  │   Logic    │  │  Breaker   │   │       │\n18: │  │  └────────────┘  └────────────┘  └────────────┘   │       │\n19: │  └───────────────────────────────────────────────────┘       │\n20: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n21:                               │\n22:                               ▼\n23:                     ┌─────────────────────┐\n24:                     │   AgentRuntime API  │\n25:                     └─────────────────────┘\n26: ```\n27: \n28: ## Design Principles\n29: \n30: 1. **Pythonic API**: Follow Python conventions and best practices\n31: 2. **Type Safety**: Full type hints and Pydantic validation\n32: 3. **Async-First**: Support both sync and async patterns\n33: 4. **Fail-Fast**: Clear exceptions with actionable error messages\n34: 5. **Observability**: Built-in logging and event streaming\n35: \n36: ## Class Design\n37: \n38: ### AgentRuntimeClient\n39: \n40: ```python\n41: class AgentRuntimeClient:\n42:     \"\"\"Client for interacting with the AgentRuntime service.\"\"\"\n43:     \n44:     def __init__(\n45:         self,\n46:         base_url: str,\n47:         api_key: Optional[str] = None,\n48:         timeout: float = 30.0,\n49:         max_retries: int = 3\n50:     ):\n51:         ...\n52:     \n53:     def create_agent(self, config: AgentConfig) -> Agent:\n54:         \"\"\"Create a new agent.\"\"\"\n55:         ...\n56:     \n57:     async def acreate_agent(self, config: AgentConfig) -> Agent:\n58:         \"\"\"Async create a new agent.\"\"\"\n59:         ...\n60: ```\n61: \n62: ### Error Handling Strategy\n63: \n64: - Custom exception hierarchy for different error types\n65: - Automatic retry with exponential backoff for transient errors\n66: - Circuit breaker pattern for cascading failure prevention\n67: \n68: ## Data Flow\n69: \n70: 1. User calls client method with Pydantic model parameters\n71: 2. Request is serialized and validated\n72: 3. Transport layer sends request with retry logic\n73: 4. Response is deserialized into Pydantic models\n74: 5. Result or exception is returned to user\n\n(End of file - total 74 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-028 Design: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    AgentRuntimeClient                        │\n│  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐       │\n│  │ Sync Client  │  │ Async Client │  │  Streaming   │       │\n│  └──────┬───────┘  └──────┬───────┘  └──────┬───────┘       │\n│         └──────────────────┴──────────────────┘              │\n│                            │                                 │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────┴─────────────────────────┐       │\n│  │              Transport Layer (HTTP/gRPC)           │       │\n│  │  ┌────────────┐  ┌────────────┐  ┌────────────┐   │       │\n│  │  │  Request   │  │   Retry    │  │  Circuit   │   │       │\n│  │  │  Builder   │  │   Logic    │  │  Breaker   │   │       │\n│  │  └────────────┘  └────────────┘  └────────────┘   │       │\n│  └───────────────────────────────────────────────────┘       │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/design.md","time":{"start":1775906932701,"end":1775906932724}}}}
