{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775907210585,"sessionID":"ses_283b3175effeZmoEnkR6wnhZW5","part":{"id":"prt_d7c4dae4b0016jQy4CXwUppW45","messageID":"msg_d7c4d7168001hKLkPFKGuZEr8F","sessionID":"ses_283b3175effeZmoEnkR6wnhZW5","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:11","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-029/delta-spec.md","content":"# AR-029 Delta Specification: SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document specifies the delta changes required to implement the low-level HTTP client foundation for the sdk-python module.\n\n## New Components\n\n### 1. HTTPClient Class\n\n**Location:** `sdk-python/src/agentcube/http/client.py`\n\n**Description:** Main HTTP client class providing sync and async HTTP operations.\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- `request(method: str, url: str, **kwargs) -> Response`\n- `get(url: str, **kwargs) -> Response`\n- `post(url: str, **kwargs) -> Response`\n- `put(url: str, **kwargs) -> Response`\n- `patch(url: str, **kwargs) -> Response`\n- `delete(url: str, **kwargs) -> Response`\n- `close() -> None`\n- `__enter__() / __exit__()` - context manager support\n- `__aenter__() / __aexit__()` - async context manager support\n\n### 2. AsyncHTTPClient Class\n\n**Location:** `sdk-python/src/agentcube/http/client.py`\n\n**Description:** Async-only HTTP client for high-performance scenarios.\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- `arequest(method: str, url: str, **kwargs) -> Response`\n- `aget(url: str, **kwargs) -> Response`\n- `apost(url: str, **kwargs) -> Response`\n- `aput(url: str, **kwargs) -> Response`\n- `apatch(url: str, **kwargs) -> Response`\n- `adelete(url: str, **kwargs) -> Response`\n- `aclose() -> None`\n\n### 3. Authentication Middleware\n\n**Location:** `sdk-python/src/agentcube/http/auth.py`\n\n**Description:** Authentication handlers for API keys and Bearer tokens.\n\n**Classes:**\n- `AuthMiddleware` (base)\n- `APIKeyAuth`\n- `BearerTokenAuth`\n- `NoAuth`\n\n### 4. Retry Configuration\n\n**Location:** `sdk-python/src/agentcube/http/retry.py`\n\n**Description:** Retry strategies and configuration.\n\n**Classes:**\n- `RetryConfig`\n- `RetryStrategy` (enum: EXPONENTIAL, LINEAR, FIXED)\n- `RetryPolicy`\n\n### 5. HTTP Exceptions\n\n**Location:** `sdk-python/src/agentcube/http/exceptions.py`\n\n**Description:** HTTP-specific exception hierarchy.\n\n**Classes:**\n- `HTTPError` (base)\n- `ConnectionError`\n- `TimeoutError`\n- `RedirectError`\n- `StatusCodeError` (with 4xx/5xx subclasses)\n\n### 6. Response Wrapper\n\n**Location:** `sdk-python/src/agentcube/http/response.py`\n\n**Description:** Response object wrapper with utility methods.\n\n**Classes:**\n- `Response`\n- `StreamingResponse`\n\n### 7. Request Builder\n\n**Location:** `sdk-python/src/agentcube/http/request.py`\n\n**Description:** Request construction utilities.\n\n**Classes:**\n- `Request`\n- `RequestBuilder`\n\n## Modified Components\n\nNone - this is a new feature implementation.\n\n## Interface Contracts\n\n### HTTP Methods\n\nThe client will support standard HTTP methods:\n\n- `GET` - Retrieve resources\n- `POST` - Create resources\n- `PUT` - Update resources (full)\n- `PATCH` - Update resources (partial)\n- `DELETE` - Remove resources\n\n### Configuration Options\n\n```python\nHTTPClientConfig(\n    base_url: str = \"\",\n    timeout: float = 30.0,\n    connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n    read_timeout: float = 30.0,\n    max_connections: int = 100,\n    max_keepalive: int = 20,\n    retry_config: RetryConfig = RetryConfig(),\n    auth: AuthMiddleware = NoAuth(),\n    headers: Dict[str, str] = {},\n    follow_redirects: bool = True,\n    verify_ssl: bool = True,\n)\n```\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- `httpx>=0.25.0` - HTTP client (sync + async)\n- `pydantic>=2.0.0` - Configuration models\n- `tenacity>=8.2.0` - Retry logic\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/spec.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-029/delta-spec.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-029/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775907210550,"end":1775907210583}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775907210587,"sessionID":"ses_283b3175effeZmoEnkR6wnhZW5","part":{"id":"prt_d7c4e0c3d001o3x3h3C7g14bXk","messageID":"msg_d7c4d7168001hKLkPFKGuZEr8F","sessionID":"ses_283b3175effeZmoEnkR6wnhZW5","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:12","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-029/design.md","content":"# AR-029 Design: SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                     HTTP Client Layer                            │\n│  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐                      │\n│  │   HTTPClient     │  │ AsyncHTTPClient  │                      │\n│  │   (Sync + Async) │  │   (Async Only)   │                      │\n│  └────────┬─────────┘  └────────┬─────────┘                      │\n│           └─────────────────────┘                                │\n│                         │                                        │\n│  ┌──────────────────────┴──────────────────────┐                │\n│  │              Transport Layer                │                │\n│  │  ┌──────────┐ ┌──────────┐ ┌──────────┐   │                │\n│  │  │ Connection│ │  Retry   │ │   Auth   │   │                │\n│  │  │  Pool     │ │  Logic   │ │Middleware│   │                │\n│  │  └──────────┘ └──────────┘ └──────────┘   │                │\n│  │  ┌──────────┐ ┌──────────┐ ┌──────────┐   │                │\n│  │  │ Request  │ │ Response │ │  Hooks   │   │                │\n│  │  │ Builder  │ │ Wrapper  │ │          │   │                │\n│  │  └──────────┘ └──────────┘ └──────────┘   │                │\n│  └───────────────────────────────────────────┘                │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                              │\n                              ▼\n                    ┌─────────────────┐\n                    │   HTTP Server   │\n                    └─────────────────┘\n```\n\n## Design Principles\n\n1. **Unified API**: Same interface for sync and async operations\n2. **Composability**: Middleware pattern for extensibility\n3. **Resource Management**: Proper connection pooling and cleanup\n4. **Fail-Fast**: Clear exceptions with contextual information\n5. **Observability**: Request/response logging and metrics hooks\n\n## Class Design\n\n### HTTPClient\n\n```python\nclass HTTPClient:\n    \"\"\"Unified HTTP client with sync and async support.\"\"\"\n    \n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        base_url: str = \"\",\n        auth: Optional[AuthMiddleware] = None,\n        timeout: float = 30.0,\n        retry_config: Optional[RetryConfig] = None,\n        headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n    ):\n        ...\n    \n    def request(self, method: str, path: str, **kwargs) -> Response:\n        \"\"\"Make a synchronous HTTP request.\"\"\"\n        ...\n    \n    async def arequest(self, method: str, path: str, **kwargs) -> Response:\n        \"\"\"Make an asynchronous HTTP request.\"\"\"\n        ...\n    \n    def close(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Close sync client and connection pool.\"\"\"\n        ...\n    \n    async def aclose(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Close async client and connection pool.\"\"\"\n        ...\n```\n\n### Auth Middleware\n\n```python\nclass AuthMiddleware(ABC):\n    \"\"\"Base class for authentication middleware.\"\"\"\n    \n    @abstractmethod\n    def apply(self, request: Request) -> Request:\n        \"\"\"Apply authentication to the request.\"\"\"\n        ...\n\nclass BearerTokenAuth(AuthMiddleware):\n    \"\"\"Bearer token authentication.\"\"\"\n    \n    def __init__(self, token: str):\n        self.token = token\n    \n    def apply(self, request: Request) -> Request:\n        request.headers[\"Authorization\"] = f\"Bearer {self.token}\"\n        return request\n```\n\n### Retry Strategy\n\n```python\nclass RetryConfig:\n    \"\"\"Configuration for retry behavior.\"\"\"\n    \n    max_attempts: int = 3\n    strategy: RetryStrategy = RetryStrategy.EXPONENTIAL\n    base_delay: float = 1.0\n    max_delay: float = 60.0\n    retryable_status_codes: Set[int] = {429, 500, 502, 503, 504}\n    retryable_exceptions: Set[Type[Exception]] = {ConnectionError, TimeoutError}\n```\n\n## Data Flow\n\n1. User calls `client.get(\"/api/resource\")`\n2. Request builder constructs full URL and headers\n3. Auth middleware adds authentication headers\n4. Retry wrapper executes request with retry logic\n5. HTTPX client sends request through connection pool\n6. Response wrapper processes HTTPX response\n7. Result or exception returned to user\n\n## Error Handling Strategy\n\n- Network errors → `ConnectionError`\n- Timeout errors → `TimeoutError`\n- 4xx errors → `ClientError` (with specific subclasses)\n- 5xx errors → `ServerError` (retryable by default)\n- Redirect errors → `RedirectError`\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/spec.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-029/design.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-029/design.md","time":{"start":1775907210556,"end":1775907210585}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775907210588,"sessionID":"ses_283b3175effeZmoEnkR6wnhZW5","part":{"id":"prt_d7c4e737f001FsBjmBFA9GAiu3","messageID":"msg_d7c4d7168001hKLkPFKGuZEr8F","sessionID":"ses_283b3175effeZmoEnkR6wnhZW5","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:13","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-029/plan.md","content":"# AR-029 Implementation Plan: SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n\n## Phase 1: Foundation (Day 1)\n\n### Tasks\n1. **Setup project structure**\n   - Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/http/` directory\n   - Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/http/__init__.py`\n   - Create module structure files\n\n2. **Define configuration models**\n   - Implement `HTTPClientConfig` model\n   - Implement `RetryConfig` model\n   - Define `RetryStrategy` enum\n\n3. **Implement exception hierarchy**\n   - Create base `HTTPError`\n   - Create specific exception classes\n   - Add HTTP status code mapping\n\n## Phase 2: Core HTTP Client (Day 1-2)\n\n### Tasks\n1. **Implement request builder**\n   - Create `Request` dataclass\n   - Create `RequestBuilder` with URL construction\n   - Add header normalization\n\n2. **Implement response wrapper**\n   - Create `Response` class\n   - Add JSON parsing helper\n   - Add error detection\n\n3. **Implement authentication middleware**\n   - Create `AuthMiddleware` base class\n   - Implement `APIKeyAuth`\n   - Implement `BearerTokenAuth`\n\n4. **Implement retry logic**\n   - Create retry decorator/policies\n   - Configure exponential backoff\n   - Define retryable vs non-retryable errors\n\n## Phase 3: HTTP Client Implementation (Day 2)\n\n### Tasks\n1. **Implement HTTPClient class**\n   - Create `HTTPClient` class\n   - Implement sync request methods (GET, POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE)\n   - Add context manager support\n\n2. **Implement AsyncHTTPClient**\n   - Create `AsyncHTTPClient` class\n   - Implement async request methods\n   - Add async context manager support\n\n3. **Add connection pooling**\n   - Configure HTTPX connection limits\n   - Implement keep-alive handling\n   - Add connection cleanup\n\n## Phase 4: Testing & Documentation (Day 3)\n\n### Tasks\n1. **Unit tests**\n   - Test client initialization\n   - Test request building\n   - Test response handling\n   - Test retry logic\n   - Test auth middleware\n   - Mock transport layer\n\n2. **Integration tests**\n   - Test against mock server\n   - Test error scenarios\n   - Test timeout handling\n\n3. **Documentation**\n   - Add docstrings to all public APIs\n   - Create usage examples\n   - Write README section\n\n## Dependencies\n\n```\nsdk-python/\n├── src/agentcube/\n│   └── http/\n│       ├── __init__.py\n│       ├── client.py\n│       ├── request.py\n│       ├── response.py\n│       ├── auth.py\n│       ├── retry.py\n│       └── exceptions.py\n```\n\n## Risk Mitigation\n\n- Use established library (httpx) for HTTP operations\n- Follow existing project patterns\n- Regular testing during development\n- Handle edge cases (timeouts, redirects, SSL)\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/spec.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-029/plan.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-029/plan.md","time":{"start":1775907210560,"end":1775907210587}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775907210590,"sessionID":"ses_283b3175effeZmoEnkR6wnhZW5","part":{"id":"prt_d7c4eb25b001MGpd5mTvVt6SSc","messageID":"msg_d7c4d7168001hKLkPFKGuZEr8F","sessionID":"ses_283b3175effeZmoEnkR6wnhZW5","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:14","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-029/tasks.md","content":"# AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n\n> **AR ID:** AR-029\n> **Module:** `sdk-python`\n> **Language:** Python\n> **Size:** M\n> **Stage:** ST-3 (Design Completed)\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nImplement the low-level HTTP client foundation for the sdk-python module. This component provides a robust, reusable HTTP client layer that handles connection management, request/response handling, authentication, retry logic, and error handling. It serves as the transport foundation for all high-level SDK clients.\n\n---\n\n## ST-3.1 — Project Structure Setup\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 3.1.1 | Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/http/` directory | Directory exists | 0.1h |\n| 3.1.2 | Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/http/__init__.py` | File exists with exports | 0.1h |\n| 3.1.3 | Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/http/client.py` | File exists | 0.1h |\n| 3.1.4 | Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/http/request.py` | File exists | 0.1h |\n| 3.1.5 | Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/http/response.py` | File exists | 0.1h |\n| 3.1.6 | Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/http/auth.py` | File exists | 0.1h |\n| 3.1.7 | Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/http/retry.py` | File exists | 0.1h |\n| 3.1.8 | Create `sdk-python/src/agentcube/http/exceptions.py` | File exists | 0.1h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Project structure ready for implementation.\n\n---\n\n## ST-3.2 — Configuration Models\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 3.2.1 | Create `HTTPClientConfig` Pydantic model | base_url, timeout, headers fields | 0.5h |\n| 3.2.2 | Add connection pool settings to config | max_connections, max_keepalive | 0.25h |\n| 3.2.3 | Add SSL verification options | verify_ssl, ssl_cert fields | 0.25h |\n| 3.2.4 | Create `RetryConfig` Pydantic model | max_attempts, strategy fields | 0.5h |\n| 3.2.5 | Define `RetryStrategy` enum | EXPONENTIAL, LINEAR, FIXED | 0.25h |\n| 3.2.6 | Add retryable status codes config | retryable_status_codes: Set[int] | 0.25h |\n| 3.2.7 | Add JSON schema export for configs | `.model_json_schema()` works | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Configuration models defined with validation.\n\n---\n\n## ST-3.3 — Exception Hierarchy\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 3.3.1 | Implement `HTTPError` base exception | Base class with message, code attrs | 0.25h |\n| 3.3.2 | Implement `ConnectionError` (network) | Raised on transport failures | 0.25h |\n| 3.3.3 | Implement `TimeoutError` (timeout) | Raised on request timeout | 0.25h |\n| 3.3.4 | Implement `RedirectError` (redirects) | Raised on redirect errors | 0.25h |\n| 3.3.5 | Implement `StatusCodeError` (4xx/5xx) | Base for HTTP status errors | 0.25h |\n| 3.3.6 | Implement `ClientError` (4xx) subclass | BadRequest, Unauthorized, etc. | 0.5h |\n| 3.3.7 | Implement `ServerError` (5xx) subclass | Server errors, retryable | 0.25h |\n| 3.3.8 | Add HTTP status code mapping | status_code -> exception class | 0.25h |\n| 3.3.9 | Export all exceptions from `exceptions.py` | Import works | 0.1h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Exception hierarchy defined and exportable.\n\n---\n\n## ST-3.4 — Request Builder\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 3.4.1 | Create `Request` dataclass | method, url, headers, body fields | 0.25h |\n| 3.4.2 | Create `RequestBuilder` class | Builder pattern implementation | 0.25h |\n| 3.4.3 | Implement URL construction | Base URL + path joining | 0.5h |\n| 3.4.4 | Implement header normalization | Case-insensitive header dict | 0.25h |\n| 3.4.5 | Implement query parameter handling | Query string construction | 0.25h |\n| 3.4.6 | Implement JSON body serialization | Content-Type handling | 0.25h |\n| 3.4.7 | Implement multipart/form-data support | File upload preparation | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Request builder functional.\n\n---\n\n## ST-3.5 — Response Wrapper\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 3.5.1 | Create `Response` class | Wraps httpx.Response | 0.25h |\n| 3.5.2 | Implement `.json()` method | JSON parsing with error handling | 0.25h |\n| 3.5.3 | Implement `.text` property | UTF-8 text decoding | 0.1h |\n| 3.5.4 | Implement `.status_code` property | HTTP status code | 0.1h |\n| 3.5.5 | Implement `.headers` property | Response headers | 0.1h |\n| 3.5.6 | Implement `.is_success` property | 2xx check | 0.1h |\n| 3.5.7 | Implement `.raise_for_status()` method | Exception on error status | 0.25h |\n| 3.5.8 | Create `StreamingResponse` class | Iterator for streaming data | 0.5h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Response wrapper complete.\n\n---\n\n## ST-3.6 — Authentication Middleware\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 3.6.1 | Create `AuthMiddleware` ABC | Abstract apply method | 0.25h |\n| 3.6.2 | Implement `APIKeyAuth` | Header or query param API key | 0.5h |\n| 3.6.3 | Implement `BearerTokenAuth` | Authorization: Bearer header | 0.25h |\n| 3.6.4 | Implement `NoAuth` | No-op middleware | 0.1h |\n| 3.6.5 | Export auth classes from `auth.py` | Import works | 0.1h |\n| 3.6.6 | Add auth to request builder integration | Auth applied before sending | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Auth middleware functional.\n\n---\n\n## ST-3.7 — Retry Logic Implementation\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 3.7.1 | Create `RetryPolicy` class | Policy with config | 0.25h |\n| 3.7.2 | Implement exponential backoff | Delay calculation | 0.5h |\n| 3.7.3 | Implement linear backoff | Delay calculation | 0.25h |\n| 3.7.4 | Implement fixed backoff | Delay calculation | 0.25h |\n| 3.7.5 | Define retryable exceptions | ConnectionError, TimeoutError | 0.25h |\n| 3.7.6 | Define retryable status codes | 429, 5xx codes | 0.25h |\n| 3.7.7 | Create retry decorator/wrapper | Apply to client methods | 0.5h |\n| 3.7.8 | Add retry logging | Log attempts with level INFO | 0.25h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Retry logic functional.\n\n---\n\n## ST-3.8 — HTTPClient Sync Implementation\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 3.8.1 | Create `HTTPClient` class | Class defined | 0.25h |\n| 3.8.2 | Implement `__init__()` with config | Attributes stored | 0.5h |\n| 3.8.3 | Implement sync `request()` method | Generic request handler | 0.5h |\n| 3.8.4 | Implement `get()` method | HTTP GET | 0.25h |\n| 3.8.5 | Implement `post()` method | HTTP POST | 0.25h |\n| 3.8.6 | Implement `put()` method | HTTP PUT | 0.25h |\n| 3.8.7 | Implement `patch()` method | HTTP PATCH | 0.25h |\n| 3.8.8 | Implement `delete()` method | HTTP DELETE | 0.25h |\n| 3.8.9 | Implement context manager | `__enter__`, `__exit__` | 0.25h |\n| 3.8.10 | Implement `close()` method | Connection cleanup | 0.25h |\n| 3.8.11 | Export from `client.py` | Import works | 0.1h |\n\n**Deliverable:** Sync HTTP client complete.\n\n---\n\n## ST-3.9 — AsyncHTTPClient Implementation\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|\n| 3.9.1 | Create `AsyncHTTPClient` class | Class defined | 0.25h |\n| 3.9.2 | Implement `__init__()` with async config | Async client initialized | 0.5h |\n| 3.9.3 | Implement async `arequest()` method | Generic async request | 0.5h |\n| 3.9.4 | Implement `aget()` method | Async HTTP GET | 0.25h |\n| 3.9.5 | Implement `apost()` method | Async HTTP POST | 0.25h |\n| 3.9.6 | Implement `aput()` method | Async HTTP PUT | 0.25h |\n| 3.9.7 | Implement `apatch()` method | Async HTTP PATCH | 0.25h |\n| 3.9.8 | Implement `adelete()` method