r, ConnectionError, TimeoutError\"\n\n# Unit test verification\npytest sdk-python/tests/unit/http/ -v\n\n# Integration tests\npytest sdk-python/tests/integration/test_http_integration.py -v\n\n# Coverage report\npytest --cov=agentcube.http --cov-report=term-missing\n\n# Lint verification\nruff check sdk-python/src/agentcube/http/\nmypy sdk-python/src/agentcube/http/\n```\n\n---\n\n## Definition of Done\n\n- [ ] All 140 tasks complete\n- [ ] Package installs successfully\n- [ ] HTTPClient importable from `agentcube.http`\n- [ ] AsyncHTTPClient importable from `agentcube.http`\n- [ ] All unit tests pass (>80% coverage)\n- [ ] All integration tests pass\n- [ ] Type checking passes (`mypy`)\n- [ ] Linting passes (`ruff`)\n- [ ] Documentation complete with docstrings\n- [ ] Usage examples in README\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- `httpx>=0.25.0` — HTTP client (sync + async)\n- `pydantic>=2.0.0` — Data validation (already in pyproject.toml)\n- `tenacity>=8.2.0` — Retry logic\n- `pytest>=7.4.0` — Testing framework (already present)\n- `pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0` — Async test support\n- `pytest-httpx>=0.22.0` — HTTP mocking for tests\n- `respx>=0.20.0` — HTTPX async mocking\n\n---\n\n## Notes\n\n- Follow existing code style in sdk-python\n- Ensure type hints on all public methods\n- Use `httpx` for both sync and async HTTP (unified API)\n- Keep configuration immutable where possible\n- Document all raised exceptions in docstrings\n- HTTP client should be reusable across multiple high-level clients\n\n---\n\n*AR-029 — Module: sdk-python — Language: Python — Size: M*\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/spec.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-029/tasks.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-k