{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775907210592,"sessionID":"ses_283b3175effeZmoEnkR6wnhZW5","part":{"id":"prt_d7c50e87a001NTOUV9ZAWBo22c","messageID":"msg_d7c4d7168001hKLkPFKGuZEr8F","sessionID":"ses_283b3175effeZmoEnkR6wnhZW5","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:15","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-029/tests.md","content":"# AR-029 Test Specification: SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n\n## Test Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n#### 1. Configuration Tests\n- Test `HTTPClientConfig` validation\n  - Valid configurations pass\n  - Invalid configurations raise ValidationError\n  - Default values applied correctly\n  - Connection pool settings validated\n\n- Test `RetryConfig` validation\n  - Retry strategy enum validation\n  - Max attempts bounds checking\n  - Delay settings validation\n\n#### 2. Request Builder Tests\n- Test URL construction\n  - Base URL + path joining\n  - Query parameter encoding\n  - URL with special characters\n\n- Test header handling\n  - Case-insensitive header dict\n  - Content-Type default handling\n  - Custom headers merged\n\n- Test request body serialization\n  - JSON body encoding\n  - Form data encoding\n  - Empty body handling\n\n#### 3. Response Wrapper Tests\n- Test response parsing\n  - JSON response parsing\n  - Text response decoding\n  - Binary response handling\n\n- Test error detection\n  - 2xx status = success\n  - 4xx raises ClientError\n  - 5xx raises ServerError\n  - `raise_for_status()` behavior\n\n#### 4. Authentication Tests\n- Test `APIKeyAuth` (header mode)\n  - API key added to Authorization header\n  - Custom header name support\n\n- Test `APIKeyAuth` (query mode)\n  - API key added to query string\n  - Existing query params preserved\n\n- Test `BearerTokenAuth`\n  - Bearer token formatted correctly\n  - Header injection works\n\n#### 5. Retry Logic Tests\n- Test exponential backoff calculation\n- Test max retry limit\n- Test non-retryable errors (4xx)\n- Test retryable errors (5xx, 429)\n- Test retry exhaustion\n\n#### 6. Sync Client Tests\n- Test client initialization\n  - With default config\n  - With custom config\n  - With authentication\n\n- Test HTTP methods\n  - GET request success\n  - POST with JSON body\n  - PUT with data\n  - PATCH with partial data\n  - DELETE request\n\n- Test error handling\n  - Connection errors\n  - Timeout errors\n  - HTTP error status codes\n\n#### 7. Async Client Tests\n- Test async client initialization\n- Test all HTTP methods async variants\n- Test concurrent requests\n- Test async context manager\n\n#### 8. Exception Tests\n- Test exception hierarchy\n- Test HTTP status code mapping\n- Test exception attributes (status_code, message)\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n#### 1. Mock Server Tests\n- Test full request lifecycle\n- Test with mocked responses\n- Test error scenarios\n- Test timeout scenarios\n\n#### 2. End-to-End Flow\n- Create client → Make request → Parse response → Close client\n- Test with authentication\n- Test with retry logic\n\n## Test Coverage Goals\n\n- Overall coverage: >= 80%\n- Client methods: 100%\n- Configuration models: 100%\n- Error handling: 100%\n- Auth middleware: 100%\n\n## Test Files Structure\n\n```\nsdk-python/tests/\n├── unit/\n│   └── http/\n│       ├── __init__.py\n│       ├── test_config.py\n│       ├── test_request.py\n│       ├── test_response.py\n│       ├── test_auth.py\n│       ├── test_retry.py\n│       ├── test_client.py\n│       ├── test_async_client.py\n│       └── test_exceptions.py\n├── integration/\n│   └── test_http_integration.py\n└── fixtures/\n    └── http_responses.json\n```\n\n## Key Test Cases\n\n### TC001: Create HTTPClient with Config\n```python\nconfig = HTTPClientConfig(\n    base_url=\"https://api.example.com\",\n    timeout=30.0,\n    max_connections=100\n)\nclient = HTTPClient(config=config)\nassert client.base_url == \"https://api.example.com\"\n```\n\n### TC002: GET Request Success\n```python\nclient = HTTPClient(base_url=\"http://localhost:8080\")\nresponse = client.get(\"/api/resource\")\nassert response.status_code == 200\nassert response.json() == {\"id\": 1, \"name\": \"test\"}\n```\n\n### TC003: POST with JSON Body\n```python\nclient = HTTPClient(base_url=\"http://localhost:8080\")\nresponse = client.post(\"/api/resource\", json={\"name\": \"new\"})\nassert response.status_code == 201\n```\n\n### TC004: Authentication Header\n```python\nauth = BearerTokenAuth(token=\"secret123\")\nclient = HTTPClient(base_url=\"http://localhost:8080\", auth=auth)\n# Request should include Authorization: Bearer secret123\n```\n\n### TC005: Retry on Server Error\n```python\n# Mock server to return 503 twice, then 200\nclient = HTTPClient(base_url=\"http://localhost:8080\", retry_config=RetryConfig(max_attempts=3))\nresponse = client.get(\"/api/resource\")  # Should retry and eventually succeed\nassert response.status_code == 200\n```\n\n### TC006: Timeout Error\n```python\nclient = HTTPClient(base_url=\"http://localhost:8080\", timeout=0.001)\nwith pytest.raises(TimeoutError):\n    client.get(\"/slow-endpoint\")\n```\n\n### TC007: Async Client Flow\n```python\nasync def test_async_get():\n    async with AsyncHTTPClient(base_url=\"http://localhost:8080\") as client:\n        response = await client.aget(\"/api/resource\")\n        assert response.status_code == 200\n```\n\n### TC008: Context Manager Cleanup\n```python\nwith HTTPClient(base_url=\"http://localhost:8080\") as client:\n    response = client.get(\"/api/resource\")\n# Client should be closed after exiting context\n```\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/spec.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-029/tests.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-029/tests.md","time":{"start":1775907210568,"end":1775907210591}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775907210593,"sessionID":"ses_283b3175effeZmoEnkR6wnhZW5","part":{"id":"prt_d7c515ca4001OiJ2TzwmthFM8V","messageID":"msg_d7c4d7168001hKLkPFKGuZEr8F","sessionID":"ses_283b3175effeZmoEnkR6wnhZW5","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:16","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-029/notes.md","content":"# AR-029 Notes: SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n\n## Created\nDate: 2026-04-11\n\n## Context\n\nThis change implements the low-level HTTP client foundation for the sdk-python module. This is the transport layer that all high-level SDK clients will build upon. It needs to be robust, well-tested, and provide a clean API for both synchronous and asynchronous operations.\n\n## Design Decisions\n\n### HTTP Library Choice\n- **httpx**: Chosen for unified sync/async API, modern design, excellent performance\n- Considered `requests` but lacks native async support\n- Considered `aiohttp` but API differs between sync/async\n\n### Authentication Pattern\n- Middleware pattern allows custom auth implementations\n- Built-in support for API key and Bearer token (most common)\n- Easy to extend for OAuth, HMAC, etc.\n\n### Retry Strategy\n- Configurable retry policies with exponential backoff\n- Default retry on 5xx and 429 (rate limit)\n- No retry on 4xx (client errors) except 429\n\n### Connection Management\n- HTTPX handles connection pooling automatically\n- Expose configuration options for pool size and keep-alive\n- Proper cleanup in context managers\n\n## Open Questions\n\n1. Should we support HTTP/2? (httpx supports it)\n2. Do we need proxy support in initial implementation?\n3. Should we include request/response logging by default?\n4. What metrics/tracing hooks should we expose?\n\n## References\n\n- Project: agentcube\n- Module: sdk-python\n- Language: Python 3.9+\n- Related: AR-028 (higher-level AgentRuntimeClient will use this HTTP client)\n\n## Dependencies\n\nThis AR provides the foundation for:\n- AR-028: AgentRuntimeClient (depends on HTTP client)\n- Future SDK clients that need HTTP transport\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/spec.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-029/notes.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-029/notes.md","time":{"start":1775907210572,"end":1775907210592}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775907210960,"sessionID":"ses_283b3175effeZmoEnkR6wnhZW5","part":{"id":"prt_d7c4d7d4b0019wxwDqMbgSVeoa","messageID":"msg_d7c4d7168001hKLkPFKGuZEr8F","sessionID":"ses_283b3175effeZmoEnkR6wnhZW5","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:10","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-029/spec.yaml","content":"id: AR-029\ntitle: SDK HTTP 底层客户端\nmodule: sdk-python\nlanguage: Python\nsize: M\nstatus: open\n\n# AR-029: SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n# Module: sdk-python\n# Language: Python\n# Size: M\n\n# OpenSpec Metadata\nopenspec:\n  version: \"1.0\"\n  project: agentcube\n\n# Architecture Requirement\nrequirement:\n  type: client-sdk\n  description: |\n    Implement the low-level HTTP client foundation for the sdk-python module.\n    This component provides a robust, reusable HTTP client layer that handles\n    connection management, request/response handling, authentication, retry logic,\n    and error handling. It serves as the transport foundation for all high-level\n    SDK clients.\n\n# Scope\nscope:\n  in:\n    - HTTP client base class with sync/async support\n    - Connection pooling and session management\n    - Authentication middleware (API key, Bearer token)\n    - Request/response serialization and deserialization\n    - Retry logic with configurable strategies\n    - Error handling and HTTP status code mapping\n    - Timeout and cancellation support\n    - Request/response interceptors/hooks\n    - Comprehensive logging and tracing\n  out:\n    - High-level service-specific clients (separate ARs)\n    - WebSocket support (separate AR)\n    - GraphQL client (separate AR)\n    - CLI tooling (separate AR)\n\n# Acceptance Criteria\nacceptance:\n  - HTTP client supports both synchronous and asynchronous operations\n  - Connection pooling reduces overhead for multiple requests\n  - Authentication middleware supports API key and Bearer token patterns\n  - Retry logic configurable with exponential backoff and max attempts\n  - HTTP errors mapped to appropriate exception types\n  - Request/response hooks allow custom middleware injection\n  - Timeout handling with proper cancellation support\n  - Unit test coverage >= 80%\n  - Type hints on all public APIs\n  - Documentation with usage examples\n\n# References\nreferences:\n  - https://www.python-httpx.org/\n  - https://docs.pydantic.dev/\n  - https://www.starlette.io/authentication/\n\n# Estimation\nestimation:\n  size: M\n  story_points: 5\n  days: 3\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-028/spec.yaml":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-029/spec.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-029/spec.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-029/spec.yaml","time":{"start":1775907210545,"end":1775907210958}}}}
